Introduction

The CatFam (Catalytic Families) database is developed for the prediction of protein
catalytic functions in the form of Enzyme Commission (EC) numbers. It consists of 
sequence profiles that are generated from enzymes annotated with the same EC number
in the Swiss-Prot database. Thus, one profile corresponds to one particular EC number. 
To predict the EC number of a query protein, the database search program catsearch.pl 
aligns a query protein with each profile in the database and finds all profiles with 
alignment score exceeding a cut-off threshold. The EC numbers of these profiles are 
then transferred to the query protein. 

The program catsearch.pl is a perl script that calls NCBI.s rpsblast to search the 
CatFam profile database and perform sequence-profile alignment. No other particular 
perl modules, such as bioperl, are required to run the program. The cut-off threshold 
is profile-specific. It is stored with each profile in the CatFam database and can be 
retrieved by the search program. The threshold is determined during the profile 
generation process and corresponds to a pre-specified nominal false positive rate (FPR). 
The corresponding FPR of the CatFam database (CatFam4D99R) released in this package is 1%. 
CatFam databases with other FPRs are available upon request. 

For more information, please refer to the paper entitled Genome-wide Enzyme Annotation 
with Precision Control:  Catalytic Families (CatFam) Databases.   

Installation

1. Unpack file catfam.tar.gz to acquire following files:

   CatFamDB/CatFam_v2.0/
	CatFam4D90R.aux
	CatFam4D90R.loo
	CatFam4D90R.lst
	CatFam4D90R.phr
	CatFam4D90R.pin
	CatFam4D90R.psd
	CatFam4D90R.psi
	CatFam4D90R.psq
	CatFam4D90R.rps
	CatFam4D95R.aux
	CatFam4D95R.loo
	CatFam4D95R.lst
	CatFam4D95R.phr
	CatFam4D95R.pin
	CatFam4D95R.psd
	CatFam4D95R.psi
	CatFam4D95R.psq
	CatFam4D95R.rps
	CatFam4D99R.aux
	CatFam4D99R.loo
	CatFam4D99R.lst
	CatFam4D99R.phr
	CatFam4D99R.pin
	CatFam4D99R.psd
	CatFam4D99R.psi
	CatFam4D99R.psq
	CatFam4D99R.rps
	release.txt
   source/
   	catsearch.pl
   	README
   	short_test.faa
   	short_test.output

2. Make sure rpsblast has been installed and runs properly. If the program is not installed, 
   please download the NCBI.s BLAST package from the FTP Site 
	ftp://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/blast/executables/release/2.2.13/ 
   and follows the instruction to install the software.  
	 	
3. Go to directory source and run following test:

   ./catsearch.pl -d ../CatFamDB/CatFam_v2.0/CatFam4D99R -i short_test.faa -o my_test.output

   The CatFam is installed successfully if the file my_test.output is created and it contains 
   the same result as the file short_test.output. 

